Lab Environment
Al Nafi provides pre-configured Ubuntu cloud machines with all necessary tools. Click Start Lab to access your environment. No additional setup required.

Task 1: Install and Configure Maigret
Step 1: Update System and Install Dependencies
sudo apt update && sudo apt upgrade -y
sudo apt install python3 python3-pip git -y
Step 2: Install Maigret
pip3 install maigret
maigret --version
Step 3: Create Working Directory Structure
mkdir -p ~/osint-lab/{results,scripts,reports}
cd ~/osint-lab
Task 2: Basic Maigret Operations
Step 1: Understand Maigret Syntax
View available options:

maigret --help
Basic syntax: maigret [options] username

Step 2: Perform Basic Username Search
Execute a search using test username:

maigret johnsmith123
This searches across 400+ platforms for the specified username.

Step 3: Save Results in Multiple Formats
maigret johnsmith123 --folderoutput ~/osint-lab/results/johnsmith123 --csv --html --json
Step 4: Configure Search Parameters
Adjust timeout and retry settings:

maigret testuser456 --timeout 30 --retries 3 --folderoutput ~/osint-lab/results/testuser456
Step 5: Use Verbose Mode for Analysis
maigret demouser789 --verbose --folderoutput ~/osint-lab/results/demouser789
